1
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,560
I now give my beloved daughter

2
00:02:55,640 --> 00:02:56,520
to the groom.

3
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:59,320
Kiss! Kiss!

4
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:06,760
Did you rape me?

5
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,640
Rape?!

6
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:09,000
What did you do to her?

7
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,680
Praya, stop!

8
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,040
Hey.

9
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:22,120
They have a secret about MP Mahasamut.

10
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,800
Tomorrow at 11 p.m.,

11
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:26,960
a female celebrity will be lured
into providing services there.

12
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,600
Yiwa!

13
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:33,520
You bastard!

14
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:40,160
Hello.

15
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,120
Is this the editorial department?

16
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,320
<i>Yes.</i>

17
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,560
May I speak to Mr. Aeywiboon, please?

18
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:49,920
<i>Mr. Aekwiboon resigned a long time ago.</i>

19
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:56,280
A long time ago?

20
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,520
<i>Yes.</i>

21
00:03:57,600 --> 00:04:00,080
<i>Around five or six years ago.</i>

22
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:02,920
I see.

23
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,920
Thank you very much. Goodbye.

24
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:09,160
That was around the same time
as the Jaiaree case.

25
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:10,960
Yes.

26
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,160
Do you like him?

27
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,840
That police captain.

28
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,840
That's none of your business.

29
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,240
What happened to your hand?

30
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,000
It's nothing.

31
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,720
What did you hit?

32
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:20,000
It's bruised this badly.
Did you crack a bone?

33
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,640
Come on. Let's go to the hospital.

34
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,480
Praya.

35
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:31,760
No matter what happens
between you and that captain,

36
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:34,800
I don't care.

37
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:38,000
As long as you don't love him.

38
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:52,600
If Mr. Wayu ends up hurting you,

39
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,640
can it be me instead?

40
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,800
Can I be the one to take care of you?

41
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,600
I'm hungry.

42
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:15,280
What do we have to eat?

43
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:16,600
Hungry at this hour?

44
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,160
It's almost ten.

45
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,520
Well, you made me exhausted
playing all day.

46
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:23,400
Besides,

47
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:25,600
since when does hunger need a schedule?

48
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,320
Eggs?

49
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:38,560
Oh?

50
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,120
I'll cook for you.

51
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:46,240
You're so nice.

52
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,440
But not for free.

53
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,920
Two kisses on the cheek.
Any more than that and I'll get shy.

54
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,280
Then I won't eat.

55
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:03,960
I'll cook for you.

56
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:09,080
Eat first, pay later. But the fee doubles.

57
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,080
You!

58
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,680
If it's not free, I'm not eating.

59
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:23,400
Hurry up too. Don't make me wait,

60
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,720
if you don't want to see me lose it.

61
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:58,040
Hot food is ready.

62
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,360
Hello, Mr. Samut.

63
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,040
What can I do for you?

64
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:49,280
You're blocking everyone
from contacting Fahsai, aren't you?

65
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,280
I know it.

66
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:55,520
Can I really stop Ms. Fahsai?

67
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:58,360
Am I that important?

68
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,200
Go get Fahsai.

69
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,120
I need to talk to her.

70
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,640
<i>No problem.</i>

71
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:05,760
<i>But…</i>

72
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,720
<i>Ms. Fahsai is asleep.</i>

73
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:17,160
We've been doing activities all day.

74
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,800
She's exhausted.

75
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,960
But you know how short honeymoons are.

76
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:25,520
We have to do every activity possible.

77
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:31,640
Tomorrow, when Ms. Fahsai wakes up,
I'll tell her to call you back.

78
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,840
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'm going to take my wife

79
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:36,080
to bed now.

80
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:13,880
I can't stand living in the same world
as you anymore, Wayu.

81
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:21,280
Mr. Samut, where are you going?

82
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:23,920
I'm going to shoot Wayu dead
with my own hands.

83
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,040
Wait, Boss.

84
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,960
What? I can't take it anymore. Move!

85
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,720
There's something more important.

86
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:45,400
They've been here a while.

87
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,800
They've walked around
almost the entire VIP zone.

88
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:57,840
Black Doc and Wayu's people?

89
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,440
What should we do, Boss?

90
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,640
Call Commander Singha.

91
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:56,560
One moment.

92
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:02,040
ROTTWEILER: STILL NO LEADS

93
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,320
Maybe we should go over there instead.

94
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:11,800
I'll give you something extra later.

95
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:15,280
Come on.

96
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,920
Why did you stop?

97
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,840
I think you should order more drinks.

98
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:43,520
That way, we can spend more time together.

99
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,000
- Okay.
- Okay?

100
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,080
Alright.

101
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,560
I'll be right back.

102
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:29,440
Found her. VIP zone, right wing.

103
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:44,600
Come.

104
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:54,720
Please cooperate.

105
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,640
Excuse us.

106
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:09,920
I happened to be inspecting
entertainment venues around here,

107
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,680
so I stopped by to inspect this place too.

108
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:15,760
No problem at all.

109
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:20,360
Take good care of the commander.

110
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:22,800
Yes, Boss.

111
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,000
This way, Commander.

112
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:47,920
Oh?

113
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:51,160
What happened?

114
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:52,920
The lady was very drunk earlier,

115
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:54,560
so we brought her here to rest.

116
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:56,320
I washed her face up already.

117
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,800
She should feel better now.

118
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:01,680
I want to go home.

119
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:03,720
Of course.

120
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,680
I'll call you a taxi.

121
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:06,720
This way, please.

122
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,200
Should we inspect
the other rooms too, Commander?

123
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:52,720
What? Was it all for nothing?

124
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,560
You risked your lives for this.

125
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,000
Hey!

126
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:16,640
This is solid evidence.

127
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:19,920
Then why the hell
are you acting all gloomy?

128
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:24,040
Had to build suspense first.

129
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:25,760
If the police hadn't shown up,

130
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:27,600
we would've gotten even stronger evidence.

131
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:29,840
They wouldn't have escaped this one.

132
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:31,880
Police?

133
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:34,640
They came to inspect the club.

134
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:37,720
They suddenly decided
to do their job tonight.

135
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:41,440
Still, I'd say
we pulled the job off pretty well.

136
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:49,760
Alright.

137
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:54,880
Here, Boss.

138
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,200
Just like I thought.

139
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:12,240
That bastard Wayu's been
stabbing me in the back all along.

140
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:14,640
Should I have the commander
arrest them now?

141
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:17,520
What's fun about just arresting them?

142
00:17:22,359 --> 00:17:24,880
You didn't die by my hand tonight…

143
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:29,880
but tomorrow, I'm gonna
make you wish you were dead,

144
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:32,080
Wayu.

145
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:05,640
You came all the way here,

146
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,680
and you're not even gonna dip
your feet in the water?

147
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:10,440
Wasn't yesterday enough already?

148
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:13,720
That was a pool. This is the ocean.

149
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,720
Well, I'm waiting
for someone to invite me.

150
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:26,680
Then how about a race?

151
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:30,520
Whoever gets their feet
in the water first wins.

152
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:35,680
And if you win, I'll return your phone.

153
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:40,680
One, two.

154
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:39,960
What happened?

155
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:44,440
- Let me see.
- Ouch.

156
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,360
A shell cut you?

157
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,960
It's okay. I can hop back myself.

158
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:53,800
Really?

159
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:55,800
At this rate, you'll bleed out.

160
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,760
Hey. Hey.

161
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:19,520
You're kind of heavy, you know.

162
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:22,040
Then put me down.

163
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:23,800
I'm just kidding.

164
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:47,200
Suddenly quiet now?

165
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,080
You like this?

166
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,040
From what I found,

167
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:15,600
this should be Aey's house.

168
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:21,480
Aey.

169
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,160
Hello.

170
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:30,600
Do you remember me?

171
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:33,680
I'm Anawin, Peekul's boyfriend.

172
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,800
Hey, I can do it myself.

173
00:22:13,360 --> 00:22:14,560
I told you already.

174
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:18,040
A captain has to take care of his crew.

175
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:29,160
Did you use to have
long hair or something?

176
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:33,440
That's what you came up with?

177
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:36,160
Well, you look pretty experienced
with the hair dryer.

178
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:37,960
A man

179
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:41,480
should know how to take care of his woman.

180
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:47,840
I'll dry it myself.

181
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:06,480
Guess I've been caught already…

182
00:23:08,040 --> 00:23:09,360
for having impure thoughts.

183
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,680
Ever since I started working,

184
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:21,200
I've risked bullets and death
more times than I can count.

185
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:25,880
But nothing's ever been harder…

186
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:28,960
than going on a fake honeymoon with you.

187
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:41,720
Can it become real?

188
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:01,240
You're kind of heavy, you know.

189
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,760
Then put me down.

190
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:05,520
I'm just kidding.

191
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,880
Kull went to Heaven Club?

192
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,120
Yes.

193
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:41,400
But we didn't tell anyone.

194
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:44,800
Kull wanted to know
why her friend killed herself

195
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,200
after coming back from that club.

196
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:49,360
They trick women into sleeping with them,
then blackmail them.

197
00:25:49,440 --> 00:25:50,840
They force them to entertain clients.

198
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:52,440
It's an entire operation.

199
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:54,720
All the evidence is in this camera.

200
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:57,960
This is huge, Kul.
What are you gonna do now?

201
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:03,400
Should we give it to the boss?

202
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:09,360
There's only one person I trust with this.

203
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:12,800
He's my dad's close friend from school.

204
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,880
That's exactly how it should be.

205
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:26,400
Good people take responsibility
for their duties.

206
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:27,800
That's what society needs.

207
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:30,480
I promise you,

208
00:26:31,080 --> 00:26:34,000
I'll bring the guilty ones to justice.

209
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:36,000
I won't let them get away with it.

210
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:38,480
I'm counting on you, Uncle.

211
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:39,960
Don't worry.

212
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,560
Your friend won't die for nothing.

213
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,080
I was outside the room.

214
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:56,680
I saw Kul hand the memory card
to Commander Singha.

215
00:26:57,760 --> 00:26:59,280
And I was shocked

216
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:02,400
that Kul and her mother
were murdered that night.

217
00:27:03,320 --> 00:27:06,560
And every media reported the same story
that it was Kul's brother who did it.

218
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:08,360
But I never believed that.

219
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:10,840
I think there was something
hidden behind all this.

220
00:27:11,360 --> 00:27:12,440
Something wasn't right.

221
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:18,360
Then why didn't you tell me
back at the funeral?

222
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:21,040
How could I tell you?

223
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:23,520
You were Captain Singha's subordinate.

224
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:29,320
And after that,

225
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:32,040
I started getting stalked.

226
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,280
I received threatening letters
several times.

227
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:35,840
Eventually, I couldn't take it anymore.

228
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:39,400
I quit my job and hid myself here.

229
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:41,200
I'm reopening the case.

230
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:44,280
Aey,

231
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:48,600
we have to bring the person
who did this to Kul to justice.

232
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:54,160
Can that really happen?

233
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,400
It's already been six years.

234
00:27:58,600 --> 00:28:00,080
He became a police commander.

235
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:03,400
And Heaven Club's backer is a minister.

236
00:28:06,840 --> 00:28:10,200
I don't know whose fault it really is
that Kul's family ended up like this.

237
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:13,240
Was it ordinary people like Kul's brother,

238
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:15,600
politicians,

239
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,200
or cops like you?

240
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:24,800
Hello, everyone.

241
00:28:24,880 --> 00:28:28,680
Today we've got a spicy clip for you.

242
00:28:28,760 --> 00:28:32,360
Spicy enough to burn the mouths
of corrupt politicians for sure.

243
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:34,160
Let's play a guessing game.

244
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:37,520
Which politician do you think
today's jackpot belongs to?

245
00:28:57,960 --> 00:28:59,080
Take care of them.

246
00:28:59,160 --> 00:29:00,160
Yes.

247
00:29:08,560 --> 00:29:09,400
Excuse me.

248
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,360
Commander,

249
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:13,360
- I have an urgent matter--
- Commander,

250
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:14,280
the team is ready, sir.

251
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,760
There's nothing more urgent than this.

252
00:29:17,040 --> 00:29:18,960
You'll lead the raid operation

253
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:20,840
with Sergeant Dam's team immediately.

254
00:29:28,120 --> 00:29:29,920
Do these two gentlemen

255
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,880
look like they're helping this lady?

256
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:33,000
THE WAY SHE WALKS LOOKS FAMILIAR

257
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:34,080
POOR HER

258
00:29:35,080 --> 00:29:37,520
Aw, so optimistic.

259
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:38,920
Well,

260
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:42,200
if you agree with Siberian

261
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:45,320
and think they're helping her,
hit the heart button.

262
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:50,400
Are they helping her or slaughtering her?

263
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:51,680
Yeah.

264
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:52,920
If you think it's slaughter,

265
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:55,120
smash that angry reaction.

266
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:01,120
How many people, sir?

267
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:03,600
We received a complaint
that illegal items are being kept here.

268
00:30:04,120 --> 00:30:05,360
We'd like permission
to search the premises.

269
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:10,280
Here's the warrant.

270
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:15,880
Go.

271
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:16,960
Yes, sir.

272
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:29,080
Captain.

273
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:35,280
We found this, sir.

274
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:37,160
We apologize, everyone.

275
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:40,480
Please remain here

276
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:42,440
until the search is complete.

277
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:54,800
SOS. POLICE PLANTED DRUGS
THE OTHERS ARE LIVESTREAMING. COME HELP

278
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:56,480
MS. PRAPAI, MY BOSS

279
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:02,000
SOS. POLICE PLANTED DRUGS
THE OTHERS ARE LIVESTREAMING. COME HELP

280
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:10,040
Whoa, whoa! See?

281
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,920
Ah! See it? See it?

282
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:13,520
Let's figure out

283
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:17,080
which club this woman
is about to be sent to.

284
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:18,320
Could it be Casino M?

285
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:21,360
The one that politicians
from the pale blue party invested in?

286
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:23,480
We know somebody knows.

287
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:27,600
- Split up and search.
- Yes, sir.

288
00:31:57,040 --> 00:31:57,880
Club H?

289
00:31:58,880 --> 00:32:00,840
Oh? That club?

290
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:01,800
Yes!

291
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:05,000
Bingo!

292
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:12,600
Hey! You Mad Dogs!

293
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:13,720
Stop.

294
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:16,440
Don't move. Hands up.

295
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:26,040
Arrest them.

296
00:32:29,440 --> 00:32:30,640
Go!

297
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:33,760
Hey!

298
00:32:49,360 --> 00:32:50,360
Hey!

299
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:52,880
Whoa! Why are you shooting?

300
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:54,200
The captain said to take them alive.

301
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:58,160
Hey! Why are you shooting?
I said take them alive.

302
00:32:58,240 --> 00:32:59,520
Go!

303
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:01,280
Go.

304
00:33:02,560 --> 00:33:03,840
Hurry up.

305
00:33:04,640 --> 00:33:06,840
Hurry up.

306
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:08,920
Go! Run first!

307
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:25,560
Who told you to shoot?!

308
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:27,560
Huh?!

309
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:32,080
Come on. Go.

310
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:35,640
Go.

311
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:37,880
Hurry.

312
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:39,640
Hey! Over there!

313
00:33:43,120 --> 00:33:44,120
Hey!

314
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:48,560
Whoa.

315
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:49,920
Whoa!

316
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:51,120
Hey!

317
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:52,200
I said don't shoot.

318
00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:53,880
What's with all the shooting?

319
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:56,200
Go back the other way.

320
00:33:56,280 --> 00:33:57,600
Go!

321
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:03,160
Turn yourself in.

322
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:04,520
You're not getting away.

323
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:21,440
Pud! Pud!

324
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:31,679
Who ordered you to eliminate them?!

325
00:34:33,159 --> 00:34:35,120
Why did you take it this far?!

326
00:34:36,239 --> 00:34:37,199
Pud!

327
00:34:37,880 --> 00:34:39,360
Pud!

328
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:41,280
Go! Run first.

329
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:42,679
Go!

330
00:34:42,760 --> 00:34:43,639
Pud!

331
00:34:43,719 --> 00:34:46,080
Run first! We need to run!

332
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:47,360
Go! Hurry!

333
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:50,920
Go!

334
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:53,199
Hurry!

335
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:54,440
Hurry!

336
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:55,760
Come!

337
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:57,880
Go!

338
00:34:57,960 --> 00:34:59,080
Go!

339
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:00,680
Go!

340
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:01,920
Get in!

341
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,000
Stop!

342
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:05,960
Captain, watch out!

343
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:14,200
The suspects are cybercriminals.

344
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:16,040
You chased them down
and shot them to death.

345
00:35:16,640 --> 00:35:18,280
Don't you think that was excessive?

346
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:20,000
Why didn't you wait for my orders?

347
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:26,680
And where's Sergeant Pichai?

348
00:35:26,760 --> 00:35:28,960
How far has the pursuit gotten?

349
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:31,080
We're tracking them down, sir.

350
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:33,320
But the vehicle

351
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:34,720
used a fake license plate,

352
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:36,960
and the escape route

353
00:35:37,040 --> 00:35:38,200
had no surveillance cameras.

354
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:41,720
You reached their hideout

355
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:43,800
and still failed

356
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:45,960
and let them escape?

357
00:35:47,440 --> 00:35:50,280
Instead of blaming your own people,

358
00:35:50,360 --> 00:35:53,000
you should focus on hunting
them down and throwing them in prison!.

359
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:54,480
I'll do that, sir.

360
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:57,560
But I'll do it the way
police officers should.

361
00:35:58,600 --> 00:36:01,080
Not like hired gunmen

362
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:03,880
carrying out executions on command.

363
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:07,560
They're not just cybercriminals.

364
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:09,080
They're drug dealers.

365
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:11,520
But we don't have concrete evidence
proving they deal drugs, sir.

366
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:14,520
You found drugs in their building
and you're saying there's no evidence?

367
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:19,800
Or do you want

368
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:22,840
to take off that honorable badge

369
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:27,720
and replace it with a dog mask instead?

370
00:36:37,840 --> 00:36:39,640
Why?!

371
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:41,320
All we did was expose corrupt politicians.

372
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,800
What did we even do wrong?

373
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:47,280
It's obvious those bastards are evil!

374
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:49,800
Who the hell would even
want to do good anymore?

375
00:36:51,160 --> 00:36:53,440
You do good and end up dying for nothing?

376
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:58,080
Those bastards even killed a woman.

377
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:02,160
I'm gonna kill them!!

378
00:37:02,240 --> 00:37:03,680
They have to pay.

379
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:04,920
No, you can't, Sam.

380
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:06,280
You need to calm down first.

381
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:07,480
Sam,

382
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:09,280
even if you do this,

383
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:11,840
Pud still won't come back.

384
00:37:14,120 --> 00:37:16,520
We can't lose anyone else, Sam.

385
00:37:17,040 --> 00:37:19,280
But they have to pay!

386
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,240
They have to die!

387
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:22,880
Don't try to stop me!

388
00:37:22,960 --> 00:37:24,520
- Sam.
- If you go, you'll die for nothing.

389
00:37:27,560 --> 00:37:29,680
No matter how guilty I feel,

390
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:32,040
no matter how hurt or angry you all are,

391
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:34,320
we have to endure it.

392
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:37,680
If we let our rage turn us into mad dogs
and go after them now,

393
00:37:37,760 --> 00:37:39,080
we'll only end up dead too.

394
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:44,480
Sam.

395
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:48,640
Do you want to lie dead beside Pud,

396
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:51,080
or do you want to get revenge

397
00:37:52,800 --> 00:37:55,800
so you can bring flowers to her grave
and tell her

398
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:58,040
you finally avenged her?

399
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:01,760
You choose.

400
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:05,760
We're all devastated

401
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:08,880
that Pud died.

402
00:38:10,200 --> 00:38:12,720
And we all feel guilty too, Sam.

403
00:38:15,120 --> 00:38:16,960
But the ones

404
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:19,320
who deserve punishment

405
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:21,320
are those pieces of shit!

406
00:38:29,680 --> 00:38:31,840
They'll pay

407
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:36,240
for what they did to us.

408
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:42,680
Just wait for the right time, Sam.

409
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:07,440
- There he is.
- That's him.

410
00:39:08,040 --> 00:39:09,080
Mr. Samut,

411
00:39:09,160 --> 00:39:12,200
police found methamphetamine
at Mr. Wayu's Kon La Yum restaurant.

412
00:39:12,280 --> 00:39:14,640
He's your brother-in-law.
What are your thoughts on this?

413
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,440
I never imagined something like this

414
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:18,640
would happen to our family.

415
00:39:20,040 --> 00:39:21,880
To be honest,

416
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:25,440
I'm very worried about
my sister's mental state right now.

417
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:28,880
Do you believe Mr. Wayu
is involved with a drug ring?

418
00:39:28,960 --> 00:39:31,840
And is it possible the restaurant
was a major drug distribution hub?

419
00:39:35,520 --> 00:39:36,760
There he is.

420
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:40,240
If you have questions,
you should ask Mr. Wayu directly.

421
00:39:44,600 --> 00:39:46,880
Ask him.

422
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:51,240
Mr. Wayu.

423
00:39:51,320 --> 00:39:52,760
- Mr. Wayu.
- Please give us an interview.

424
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:55,600
Did you already know the police
found drugs at your restaurant?

425
00:39:55,680 --> 00:39:57,160
You know already, don’t you?

426
00:39:57,240 --> 00:39:59,120
- Do you know it?
- Do you?

427
00:39:59,200 --> 00:40:00,720
Please answer us.

428
00:40:00,800 --> 00:40:03,240
- Mr. Wayu.
- Did you know the Mad Dog Gang

429
00:40:03,320 --> 00:40:05,400
used your restaurant to commit cybercrimes

430
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:07,520
and that authorities
are currently hunting them down?

431
00:40:12,720 --> 00:40:15,920
According to the police investigation,

432
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:17,160
three male employees
from the restaurant are missing,

433
00:40:17,240 --> 00:40:20,560
and one female employee died at the scene.

434
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:23,520
You personally hired
all four of them, didn't you?

435
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:25,640
Sources say you were very close to them.

436
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:27,760
Did you know
they were behind the Mad Dog page?

437
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:29,400
Did you know or not? Please answer us.

438
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:31,560
- Did you know it?
- Please answer us.

439
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:38,520
Yes?

440
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:41,160
<i>The police raided the restaurant.</i>

441
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:43,680
<i>They found drugs there.</i>

442
00:40:45,120 --> 00:40:47,280
I don't know which bastard planted them.

443
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:53,040
And everyone happened
to be livestreaming at the time.

444
00:40:55,680 --> 00:40:57,480
The police chased us.

445
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:02,280
I managed to save everyone, but…

446
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:08,160
I couldn't save Pud in time.

447
00:41:08,240 --> 00:41:10,040
I couldn't save Pud in time.

448
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:16,040
Wayu,

449
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:19,160
Pud is dead.

450
00:41:23,160 --> 00:41:24,920
Pud is dead.

451
00:41:29,240 --> 00:41:30,120
Okay.

452
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:33,520
I’m taking Fahsai
back to Bangkok right now.

453
00:41:33,600 --> 00:41:34,840
We'll talk later.

454
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:46,960
I won't deny

455
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:49,920
that I personally hired those employees.

456
00:41:50,960 --> 00:41:53,440
But I have nearly 20 staff members,

457
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:55,080
not including part-timers.

458
00:41:55,160 --> 00:41:57,920
How would I know
which people you're referring to?

459
00:41:58,440 --> 00:42:00,920
The deceased employee
has already been identified.

460
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,000
Her name was Pudsorn.

461
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:11,480
You mean to tell me

462
00:42:11,560 --> 00:42:13,520
Pudsorn was part of the Mad Dog Gang?

463
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:16,080
Are you sure

464
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:17,800
there hasn't been some misunderstanding?

465
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:18,840
Yes.

466
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:21,640
Once the masks were removed,
we identified her as Ms. Pudsorn.

467
00:42:21,720 --> 00:42:25,160
The other three male employees escaped.

468
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:28,520
There was also one Mad Dog Gang member
who wasn't present during the livestream.

469
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:29,920
The one called Pitbull.

470
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:33,160
Can you think of anyone
who might be Pitbull?

471
00:42:33,240 --> 00:42:34,680
Isn't that just a dog breed?

472
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:38,680
None of my employees is named that.

473
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:42,520
And I don’t follow
or pay attention to the Mad Dog Gang.

474
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:45,120
Ms. Fahsai.

475
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:46,360
Ms. Fahsai.

476
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:48,920
Have you ever watched
the Mad Dog livestreams?

477
00:42:50,680 --> 00:42:51,880
Yes.

478
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:53,960
Have you ever seen anyone
whose behavior suggested

479
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:56,280
they might be connected to Mad Dog?

480
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:58,080
Excuse me.

481
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:00,960
Ms. Fahsai has only been
to the restaurant twice.

482
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:02,520
She doesn't even remember anyone's face.

483
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:05,360
And besides,
she has nothing to do with this.

484
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:07,000
I'd like to take her inside to rest.

485
00:43:07,080 --> 00:43:08,480
I'll come back out
and explain everything myself.

486
00:43:09,520 --> 00:43:12,360
So what's the truth?
And who are the Mad Dogs?

487
00:43:12,440 --> 00:43:14,720
Please answer us, Mr. Wayu.

488
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:16,840
Do you really don't know, Mr. Wayu?

489
00:43:16,920 --> 00:43:19,040
Mr. Wayu, can you answer the question?

490
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:20,280
Mr. Wayu.

491
00:43:20,360 --> 00:43:22,280
- Please, Mr. Wayu.
- Mr. Wayu.

492
00:43:22,360 --> 00:43:23,360
Ms. Fahsai.

493
00:43:23,440 --> 00:43:24,480
Sir.

494
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:25,840
Please answer our questions.

495
00:43:25,920 --> 00:43:27,640
How are you holding up?

496
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:28,920
You must be terrified.

497
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:30,800
Come sit down first.

498
00:43:32,120 --> 00:43:32,960
Here.

499
00:43:38,680 --> 00:43:40,280
Samut! What are you doing?

500
00:43:42,400 --> 00:43:43,200
Let go, Samut.

501
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:47,080
You think I'm the evil one?
You're even worse than me!

502
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:50,080
You drug-dealing bastard.

503
00:43:50,160 --> 00:43:52,200
And you even created a page
to slander other people.

504
00:43:52,280 --> 00:43:55,880
You're this disgusting,
and you dare mess with my sister?

505
00:43:57,160 --> 00:43:58,760
Samut, let go of me.

506
00:44:00,280 --> 00:44:01,560
- Yong.
- Yes, sir.

507
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:03,560
- Take Fahsai upstairs.
- Yes.

508
00:44:03,640 --> 00:44:04,960
No.

509
00:44:05,040 --> 00:44:06,240
I'm not going.

510
00:44:07,920 --> 00:44:08,920
I'll be fine.

511
00:44:09,920 --> 00:44:12,800
Go upstairs and rest. Trust me.

512
00:44:14,520 --> 00:44:17,560
- Yong.
- Yes, sir.

513
00:44:17,640 --> 00:44:19,400
Come on, Ms. Fahsai.

514
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:20,960
Let's go.

515
00:44:24,240 --> 00:44:27,520
Now explain. What is all this?

516
00:44:28,160 --> 00:44:30,280
And you're still asking him?

517
00:44:31,200 --> 00:44:32,520
Isn't it obvious?

518
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:35,160
Those mangy stray dogs of his

519
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:37,720
have been attacking us
from the very beginning.

520
00:44:42,080 --> 00:44:43,240
What's your plan?

521
00:44:44,360 --> 00:44:48,640
You infiltrated my family
just to frame us and destroy us?

522
00:44:50,280 --> 00:44:51,640
Who's backing you?

523
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:55,160
I asked you nicely.

524
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:57,600
Who's backing you?

525
00:44:59,840 --> 00:45:01,200
Stop!

526
00:45:02,200 --> 00:45:03,160
Jon.

527
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:04,840
Yes, sir.

528
00:45:05,880 --> 00:45:08,200
Mr. Samut, please stop.

529
00:45:08,280 --> 00:45:09,400
That's enough, sir.

530
00:45:10,440 --> 00:45:11,840
Let go of me.

531
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:17,120
I'll make him get on his knees
and confess who sent him here.

532
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:21,840
You'll ruin everything.

533
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:24,960
The reporters are still
all over the front yard.

534
00:45:26,920 --> 00:45:27,800
Go somewhere else.

535
00:45:28,840 --> 00:45:30,560
I'll talk to him myself.

536
00:45:34,280 --> 00:45:37,320
No one's going to believe
trash like you anymore.

537
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:39,960
Remember that.

538
00:45:40,920 --> 00:45:42,000
I said let me go.

539
00:45:56,840 --> 00:45:58,200
So,

540
00:45:59,400 --> 00:46:01,320
those dogs

541
00:46:01,400 --> 00:46:02,840
really are your people?

542
00:46:02,920 --> 00:46:06,480
You ordered them to keep attacking
and harassing us all this time?

543
00:46:07,120 --> 00:46:08,480
I don't know anything about this.

544
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:11,760
So it's all just a coincidence?

545
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:14,680
And don't you think
it's a little too coincidental

546
00:46:14,760 --> 00:46:17,600
that the police raided the place
while I wasn't there?

547
00:46:19,040 --> 00:46:22,360
I think someone
deliberately wanted to destroy me.

548
00:46:22,440 --> 00:46:24,280
You're accusing Samut?

549
00:46:25,320 --> 00:46:28,000
Even if he did do it, you still can't deny

550
00:46:28,920 --> 00:46:30,760
that those mangy dogs are your people.

551
00:46:33,120 --> 00:46:35,480
I'm really disappointed
that I trusted you.

552
00:46:38,360 --> 00:46:40,360
Until you clear your name,

553
00:46:41,360 --> 00:46:44,480
don't let me see your face again.
And stay away from Fahsai too.

554
00:46:45,800 --> 00:46:48,600
- Sir, but about this--
- Save your excuses

555
00:46:49,120 --> 00:46:50,840
for the reporters.

556
00:47:01,280 --> 00:47:04,000
Normally, I only go to the restaurant
two or three times a month.

557
00:47:04,640 --> 00:47:06,720
The rest is handled
by the restaurant manager.

558
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:09,480
As everyone already knows,

559
00:47:09,560 --> 00:47:11,760
I have a lot of businesses
to take care of,

560
00:47:12,360 --> 00:47:14,840
and nothing like this
has ever happened before.

561
00:47:14,920 --> 00:47:16,360
<i>Then let me ask something in return.</i>

562
00:47:16,440 --> 00:47:18,800
<i>Why did something this big</i>

563
00:47:18,880 --> 00:47:20,320
<i>happen while I wasn't there?</i>

564
00:47:21,160 --> 00:47:23,760
<i>What if someone wanted</i>
<i>to destroy my reputation</i>

565
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:26,400
<i>by planting drugs in my restaurant?</i>

566
00:47:26,480 --> 00:47:31,040
<i>So you're denying</i>
<i>all involvement in this?</i>

567
00:47:31,120 --> 00:47:33,200
<i>The drugs, the Mad Dog Gang, all of it?</i>

568
00:47:33,280 --> 00:47:34,120
<i>Right.</i>

569
00:47:34,200 --> 00:47:37,560
<i>And there was a livestream room</i>
<i>in the building. You really knew nothing?</i>

570
00:47:37,640 --> 00:47:39,320
<i>That room does exist, yes.</i>

571
00:47:40,160 --> 00:47:44,280
<i>But I set it up as a studio to film</i>
<i>promotional clips for the restaurant.</i>

572
00:47:45,960 --> 00:47:47,600
<i>I had no idea</i>

573
00:47:47,680 --> 00:47:50,720
<i>some Mad Dog group</i>
<i>was secretly using my studio.</i>

574
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:53,960
<i>That's how it is.</i>

575
00:47:54,560 --> 00:47:56,600
<i>I want to apologize to the public.</i>

576
00:47:57,120 --> 00:47:58,280
<i>I have many businesses to manage,</i>

577
00:47:58,360 --> 00:48:00,560
<i>and I may not have been able</i>
<i>to oversee everything thoroughly enough.</i>

578
00:48:02,800 --> 00:48:06,480
<i>I'm fully willing to cooperate with</i>
<i>any investigation to prove my innocence.</i>

579
00:48:07,760 --> 00:48:09,520
<i>And I want to firmly state</i>

580
00:48:11,280 --> 00:48:15,240
<i>that I have never been</i>
<i>involved with drugs,</i>

581
00:48:16,840 --> 00:48:20,000
<i>nor do I have any connection</i>
<i>whatsoever with the Mad Dog Gang.</i>

582
00:48:21,800 --> 00:48:23,920
Why the hell is he saying
all this bullshit?

583
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:25,520
He said we'd fight together,

584
00:48:26,040 --> 00:48:27,480
and now he's just abandoning us like this?

585
00:48:29,400 --> 00:48:31,400
Just because he married
a politician's daughter,

586
00:48:32,360 --> 00:48:34,240
now he's lying just like them too?

587
00:48:34,840 --> 00:48:36,040
Damn it!

588
00:48:36,120 --> 00:48:37,240
Shut up.

589
00:48:38,080 --> 00:48:41,560
I'm gonna say it!
Can't you see he used us?

590
00:48:41,640 --> 00:48:43,360
He doesn't care that the police
are hunting us down.

591
00:48:43,440 --> 00:48:46,360
He doesn't care whether
we even have a place to hide

592
00:48:46,440 --> 00:48:48,560
or whether we live or die!

593
00:48:49,560 --> 00:48:53,360
Even after Pud died,
he still doesn't care.

594
00:48:57,720 --> 00:48:58,960
He doesn't know us anymore.

595
00:48:59,600 --> 00:49:01,800
He doesn't know the Mad Dog Gang anymore!

596
00:49:06,000 --> 00:49:07,560
I'm wondering the same thing.

597
00:49:08,600 --> 00:49:09,880
What is he feeling right now?

598
00:49:10,840 --> 00:49:13,520
How could he lie to the reporters
with a straight face like that?

599
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:16,520
Does he even hurt the way we hurt?

600
00:49:17,640 --> 00:49:21,120
Does he know what it feels like to lose
someone you love right before your eyes?

601
00:49:24,400 --> 00:49:25,840
Why wouldn't he know?

602
00:49:27,040 --> 00:49:29,280
Do you think you're the only ones hurting?

603
00:49:31,120 --> 00:49:33,080
Maybe Wayu didn't see Pud die,

604
00:49:34,320 --> 00:49:35,840
but he watched his mother

605
00:49:35,920 --> 00:49:38,720
and sister get shot dead
right in front of him.

606
00:49:40,400 --> 00:49:42,280
And then he got framed

607
00:49:42,360 --> 00:49:44,640
for killing them himself.

608
00:49:47,160 --> 00:49:50,280
Isn't that enough to compare
to what you're all feeling right now?

609
00:49:56,800 --> 00:49:58,160
It's not that he doesn't hurt.

610
00:49:59,760 --> 00:50:01,320
But he endures it.

611
00:50:03,680 --> 00:50:05,600
He's been enduring it for a long time.

612
00:50:07,360 --> 00:50:09,280
Hiding your pain deep inside

613
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:13,960
hurts even more than screaming it out loud
like you guys are doing.

614
00:50:38,240 --> 00:50:40,720
I thought you were better
than those corrupt cops I've met.

615
00:50:41,320 --> 00:50:43,200
But in the end,
you're no different from them.

616
00:50:43,280 --> 00:50:45,280
A bunch of police thugs
abusing ordinary people!

617
00:50:45,360 --> 00:50:46,960
I wasn't bullying anyone.

618
00:50:47,040 --> 00:50:48,400
You're angry because I searched
your brother's restaurant,

619
00:50:49,000 --> 00:50:50,560
but I was doing my duty.

620
00:50:50,640 --> 00:50:52,600
And we really did find drugs hidden there.

621
00:50:52,680 --> 00:50:55,560
So now you're using drugs as an excuse
to shoot innocent people to death?

622
00:50:55,640 --> 00:50:56,720
You're the worst.

623
00:50:56,800 --> 00:50:58,720
You're just a politician's lapdog.

624
00:51:00,200 --> 00:51:01,240
You bastard.

625
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:03,440
I didn't want anyone to die either.

626
00:51:04,160 --> 00:51:07,160
I already reported this to my superior.

627
00:51:07,240 --> 00:51:08,280
There'll be an investigation,

628
00:51:08,360 --> 00:51:10,760
and the officers involved
will be punished.

629
00:51:11,400 --> 00:51:12,840
I'm upset about this too.

630
00:51:15,680 --> 00:51:17,960
Upset because
only one person got shot dead?

631
00:51:20,600 --> 00:51:22,480
I should never have known
someone as disgusting as you.

632
00:51:22,560 --> 00:51:25,600
And if I'm disgusting, then what about
the drugs in your brother's restaurant?

633
00:51:25,680 --> 00:51:28,520
Stop using drugs as your excuse already.

634
00:51:29,360 --> 00:51:31,120
My brother shut down every gambling den

635
00:51:31,200 --> 00:51:33,560
and loan shark operation our father had

636
00:51:34,080 --> 00:51:35,760
because he hated
dirty businesses like that.

637
00:51:38,160 --> 00:51:41,880
My brother would never sell drugs.

638
00:51:41,960 --> 00:51:43,680
You have your reasons.

639
00:51:43,760 --> 00:51:46,120
I'm doing my duty
based on the evidence I have.

640
00:51:46,200 --> 00:51:48,600
If you truly believe
your brother is innocent,

641
00:51:48,680 --> 00:51:50,800
then bring me proof.

642
00:51:50,880 --> 00:51:52,680
And even if he proves it,

643
00:51:54,240 --> 00:51:56,840
can what's already
been lost ever come back?

644
00:52:01,360 --> 00:52:03,200
You keep saying
you were just doing your duty,

645
00:52:04,320 --> 00:52:05,320
that you did nothing wrong,

646
00:52:08,160 --> 00:52:09,240
but it was wrong.

647
00:52:12,560 --> 00:52:13,680
You know why?

648
00:52:17,240 --> 00:52:19,000
It's because you don't even know
who we really are.

649
00:52:39,920 --> 00:52:41,680
Of course Wayu would deny it.

650
00:52:43,680 --> 00:52:45,480
Who would ever admit
to something like this?

651
00:52:46,960 --> 00:52:49,360
Until we know the full truth,

652
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:51,880
you're staying here.

653
00:52:52,480 --> 00:52:54,040
And you are forbidden from seeing him.

654
00:52:54,880 --> 00:52:55,840
Dad,

655
00:52:57,040 --> 00:53:00,640
from what I know about Wayu,
he's not the kind of person who'd do that.

656
00:53:01,640 --> 00:53:05,120
Besides, if the people at the restaurant
really were behind the Mad Dog page,

657
00:53:05,640 --> 00:53:07,720
didn't that page help people?

658
00:53:10,000 --> 00:53:12,360
Then what about the drugs
found in the restaurant?

659
00:53:12,880 --> 00:53:13,880
How are you going to explain that?

660
00:53:13,960 --> 00:53:16,120
Can he deny responsibility?

661
00:53:23,400 --> 00:53:24,280
And what about you?

662
00:53:25,840 --> 00:53:26,880
Can you accept it?

663
00:53:28,600 --> 00:53:32,160
Your husband's name
being blacklisted as a drug dealer?

664
00:53:35,120 --> 00:53:36,040
I can't accept it.

665
00:53:36,960 --> 00:53:39,960
Whatever you do,
think about our family's reputation too.

666
00:54:07,960 --> 00:54:08,960
Yong,

667
00:54:09,480 --> 00:54:10,760
did you leave yet?

668
00:54:11,480 --> 00:54:12,400
Huh?

669
00:54:13,160 --> 00:54:14,680
You're going to see Mr. Wayu?

670
00:55:39,320 --> 00:55:40,360
Come in.

671
00:55:51,760 --> 00:55:52,840
How did you get here?

672
00:55:59,040 --> 00:56:00,800
Your father forbade me from seeing you.

673
00:56:03,960 --> 00:56:07,560
So he probably forbade you
from seeing me too.

674
00:56:08,800 --> 00:56:10,560
No one can stop me.

675
00:56:21,560 --> 00:56:22,960
You must feel humiliated right now.

676
00:56:26,680 --> 00:56:28,760
Everyone thinks I'm a drug dealer.

677
00:56:29,960 --> 00:56:31,320
I don't believe you did it.

678
00:56:34,680 --> 00:56:36,080
I'm not a good person either.

679
00:56:38,240 --> 00:56:40,320
But you're not a bad person.

680
00:56:45,800 --> 00:56:46,840
You remember Pud, right?

681
00:56:53,400 --> 00:56:56,200
She died, and I couldn't
do anything to help her.

682
00:57:00,640 --> 00:57:02,400
Everyone got dragged into this
because of me.

683
00:57:06,720 --> 00:57:08,760
If I'd been there with them,

684
00:57:10,400 --> 00:57:11,880
things wouldn't have turned out like this.

685
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:16,760
Don't blame yourself yet. Come on.

686
00:57:17,280 --> 00:57:18,800
Please don't blame yourself.

687
00:57:35,040 --> 00:57:36,720
You shouldn't have come here.

688
00:57:44,160 --> 00:57:45,760
You'll get dragged into trouble
because of me too.

689
00:57:47,840 --> 00:57:50,600
I know exactly how you feel right now.

690
00:57:53,160 --> 00:57:56,760
I've felt this terrible before too.

691
00:57:59,960 --> 00:58:02,640
And back then, someone helped me.

692
00:58:05,320 --> 00:58:07,400
He stayed by my side.

693
00:58:12,960 --> 00:58:15,360
It meant everything to me.

694
00:58:21,600 --> 00:58:23,800
Even if I'm not a good wife,

695
00:58:27,160 --> 00:58:28,280
at the very least,

696
00:58:29,440 --> 00:58:31,160
I won't leave you alone.

697
00:59:14,440 --> 00:59:17,960
Thank you for staying by my side.
Thank you.

698
01:00:52,600 --> 01:00:55,320
Samut did this to you?

699
01:00:55,400 --> 01:00:57,400
Don't you ever hurt my daughter again.

700
01:00:58,760 --> 01:01:01,360
A piece of trash like you
deserves someone like me.

701
01:01:01,440 --> 01:01:03,280
That's what makes us a perfect match.

702
01:01:03,360 --> 01:01:05,040
I have someone who can help us.

703
01:01:09,640 --> 01:01:11,440
I just got a new piece of evidence.

704
01:01:11,520 --> 01:01:14,520
So, Commander, who exactly do you think
will end up standing trial?

705
01:01:14,600 --> 01:01:16,040
Mr. Wayu?

706
01:01:16,120 --> 01:01:17,400
Or you?

707
01:01:34,040 --> 01:01:35,400
How do you know about all this?

708
01:01:36,840 --> 01:01:38,080
This is between me and Kul.

709
01:01:38,680 --> 01:01:40,240
Because I'm not an outsider.

710
01:02:38,640 --> 01:02:42,960
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
